  "byline": "Tyler Cowen",
  "publishedAt": "2026-06-22T04:59:04.000Z",
  "contentHtml": "<p>1. Allison Schrager is very good, including her new book <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Worth-Risk-Seven-Taking-Chances/dp/0300266111/ref=sr_1_1?crid=330D5ZXMMU4LX&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.C9h1SktMC-KG2LjwY01u7h92Pwkx5K3UMM8mTaddwg5UdDbAU5txzQzsLcwWCun1xiUbihetQ8y3vPq05fyMEwt7ZVpTTVYocL66ummhfkNV4n_ItuOBXdmrHlW7PXpJRs8lARU8BtDK5cxPGVZ8j4WG7WVohCbugjFHRZkVtLwKvcnpFvjv25aZDRaZ4jH5tbI3Dmgq_E49kWT7u3aHa4zWL-VXby0-s3pn5oHI8OM.Z4k0RIeL55A2Ub6CpRAsABpPATdyAAb4CmDZHt_sbvw&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Worth+the+Risk%3A+The+Seven+Myths+that+Keep+Us+from+Taking+the+Chances+We+Need+to+Take&amp;nsdOptOutParam=true&amp;qid=1781974810&amp;sprefix=worth+the+risk+the+seven+myths+that+keep+us+from+taking+the+chances+we+need+to+take%2Caps%2C521&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Worth the Risk: The Seven Myths that Keep Us from Taking the Chances We Need to Take</a>.</p>\n<p>2. <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Dialogues-Confucius-Complete-Text/dp/0691276463/ref=sr_1_1?crid=H62CKQHV6ZHD&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.wUEc1VIXQeAn19C-htpaqVKO7FDqiqj_vdSiju6rAByuWBWwIwTDmWnYU6Qc8m4SlHONvMQNrZjbbLso4nqKoYSy5l7OylsELHrSkhqbrfeGiyLqcRtSwIplvGh25O88jaTjG-IKJQCR-NSzTj1ebLxF0aPCO2ip9wzHXOqmq2-0kQMW0dSCNEpYoJwCWOqt3O1pqIZBkYcULDiGRumrsrT7zWU0xnrjicoHMHyzMWU.ztkTie_MCXisY2xDw7YJVPyAe5kstxo2gvDjiLXVUxU&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=dialogues+of+confucius&amp;qid=1781974960&amp;sprefix=dialogues+o%2Caps%2C141&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Dialogues of Confucius</a>, translated and edited by Brian Buya and Wenwen Li.&nbsp; It seems these works, once considered doubtful in provenance, are likely by Confucius after all?&nbsp; So this is an epic volume of real import.&nbsp; But does it raise my opinion of Confucius as a thinker?&nbsp; No.</p>\n<p>3. I liked all of Thomas F. Madden’s <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Fall-Republics-Carthage-American-Constitution/dp/069119582X/ref=sr_1_1?crid=50MIVMM7L9RQ&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.yIHoWIC6GicEsI9nyZuomRqpRhVO-2IUCS8hcGhiLTY.OAs7cWTbD27jvXmsJXi7T--0pZtklJdsyCGNis-DE8I&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=The+Fall+of+Republics%3A+A+History+from+Ancient+Carthage+to+the+American+Constitution&amp;nsdOptOutParam=true&amp;qid=1781974993&amp;sprefix=the+fall+of+republics+a+history+from+ancient+carthage+to+the+american+constitution%2Caps%2C585&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">The Fall of Republics: A History from Ancient Carthage to the American Constitution</a>, but most of all the section on Venice.</p>\n<p>4. Frank Callanan, <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/James-Joyce-Political-Frank-Callanan/dp/0691227977/ref=sr_1_1?crid=3A0HP1P0YY1VA&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.RYXOPLprocXhEprjpj25cAsA0dSVQKZYgXlxdaHbUkdLF_f_TMnz7L5L_9AubarzSkRxesGItQMdvqweoLzkiNl9BMXLH1FditHTbdw5wlEdgP1fBDODtD9O1lEotmQVUXqcytfB1PWbc_aHudD5Apk6gVrr4ADz-fcxP4MmYWS4ZqMXcJ_ja_6qeSXm2HRjRD8qguHpaWMa3nYLc20j1Xo8ljdYo7bj3TVmmXbWKjw.be4QOHu2D63kWRHfgyLqIie8_0k28_bbgnCuaiLpmPg&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=james+joyce+political+life&amp;qid=1781974499&amp;sprefix=james+joyce+politica%2Caps%2C128&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">James Joyce: A Political Life</a>.&nbsp; An excellent book, and it truly induces us to revalue Joyce and understand him in a new light.&nbsp; Joyce was in fact highly politically conscious, heavily influenced by Parnellism, and in part writing a critique of Irish nationalism from an internal perspective.</p>\n<p>4. Alastair Reynolds, “<a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Zima-Other-Stories-Alastair-Reynolds/dp/1597800791/ref=sr_1_1?crid=3PT3CPCARAKM6&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.ptikmDvKslLqbZgAahx8iOIoi8nFRykMyGvaaG4cLBv4hwSKM9fztjR6anl0HJdxJLuLz0R453vJy8yF4TiJbvGZ0k2mIDhmUmxSuUF10DzTL9w6AhWKaHWbTws5zWEbf5_lvvQD1XqyKzuLDnjJB9BNgJblTHUSBwtGO2MXgMJAp-zel96BA4z3_ZiffnxSlZY5FBD0dGkUaT4IlM1ZpcHh9pNV3AtdSVnmlKmC8jgxsatfcrjBZqdWn3Lfg9CUVBth60mmG81PGZwYx-u8_mvvV7-Hbd8bkT0SHaPBv40.oMzGaTd3TnRztD0xW4f2JnLtu2AP2SoPrnDJr4JDisY&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=zima+blue&amp;qid=1781974898&amp;sprefix=zima+blue%2Caps%2C138&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Zima Blue</a>,” one of the better short stories about AI, and also aesthetics.&nbsp; Via R.</p>\n<p>5. Justin Gest, <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Democratic-Drain-Migration-Struggle-Democracy/dp/1009726919/ref=sr_1_1?crid=C596XP4WC4HO&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.fEoMp8gmjx00McOYmDssTqafzNqglw8_LyxJQaX0N-v5z-MmL0eXnLY5Z4RJ_cvXjYmy1OO9bGbYoDsCGiUjJZo6frpoH8cm6xWMhrInTXMx45Kv3gzzLKml_QnZDpaP0lSRnOBActXdfvOJStMRkJ8O5u4d3EAfp-9rx6gV3qjLlWhD3i4mO-ZLBmDH7w0Nd6Hbuzpsq-vHjInjv60aY-GlyyuDtzluvOW5qp87OVE.jMhnfw9vRAi46pDcQ9fdHmkqOyRwjG1Zw3hptOGZruM&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Democratic+Drain%3A+Global+Migration+and+the+Struggle+for+Democracy&amp;nsdOptOutParam=true&amp;qid=1781975025&amp;sprefix=tion%2Caps%2C1173&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Democratic Drain: Global Migration and the Struggle for Democracy</a> is a political economy argument that widespread immigration can drain home countries of their democracy supporters to some extent.</p>\n<p>Daniel Susskind,<a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/What-Should-My-Children-Do/dp/B0G1Y3K8X3/ref=sr_1_1?crid=86QEO8ENB7XT&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.6R7kWkZzl-7qaEQBf5_OE-EglzWVsL9n_FA17bQ0OdMB7museR6uW6kU-Fuj5wYQsaep2uxY0VBMXxxWc4WqZ1BH0a959q9YjSVTzzVe1Tb11C8BPUyFdp-aFx-1mR3PFfyrOrx6bD6N8Q6nM3s8jZvsefEfchH2LkomHDzn8tRsBtDq5-seq26jPR-lVw0274GQy-pjKoBlfqFePyKHkW5G_8ql9NCN13fG_fydUog.-ZmohDQ8-OK_-pPY98qqCdGUyqY1EpAZc_iMh4sxDyQ&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=What+Should+My+Children+Do%3F%3A+How+to+Flourish+in+the+Age+of+AI&amp;nsdOptOutParam=true&amp;qid=1781975061&amp;sprefix=what+should+my+children+do+how+to+flourish+in+the+age+of+ai%2Caps%2C333&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"> What Should My Children Do?: How to Flourish in the Age of AI</a> is a book that needed to be written.</p>\n<p>Melissa S. Kearney and Luke Pardue, editors.&nbsp; <a href=\"https://www.economicstrategygroup.org/publication/demographic-headwinds/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Demographic Headwinds: The Economic Consequences of Lower Birth Rates and Longer Lives</a>.&nbsp; A short volume, to the point, worry is in order.</p>\n<p>And there is Jeremy A. Simmons, <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Sea-Treasures-Cultural-History-Ancient/dp/0691280142/ref=sr_1_1?crid=3E1MGPWONHNUY&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.Jx8ITnKuq9dDUGEFwuXoGg.Ye5C_X3DTFX4XTiYxTcTL64E42LloXOrk7okKNfsVyU&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Sea+of+Treasures%3A+A+Cultural+History+of+Ancient+Indian+Ocean+Trade&amp;nsdOptOutParam=true&amp;qid=1781975154&amp;sprefix=sea+of+treasures+a+cultural+history+of+ancient+indian+ocean+trade%2Caps%2C106&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Sea of Treasures: A Cultural History of Ancient Indian Ocean Trade</a>.</p>",
